        "challenge": {
            "id": "chl_001",
            "name": "Strong Legs at Home",
            "description": "<p>This 5-day training plan is designed to strengthen your lower body using only your own body weight — no equipment needed. The workouts focus on your glutes, quads, hamstrings, and calves, while also improving balance, joint stability, and overall movement control. Each session lasts 20-30 minutes and can be done at home in a small space.</p><p>The plan progresses gradually by repeating basic movement patterns such as squats, lunges, bridges, and hip hinges, helping you build a strong foundation without overloading your joints. The exercises are performed in a slow and controlled manner to maximize muscle activation and avoid strain. Weekly progression comes from increasing repetitions or sets at your own pace.</p><p>This plan is suitable for beginners and intermediate levels, and doesn't require any prior experience. All you need is consistency — and your own body.</p>",
            "duration": "10d",
            "difficulty": "easy",
